* ============================================================
*  PINOCCHIO RECALL BATCHING PROOF (Phase 1.3d)
*
*  Status:  CANDIDATE / REVIEW_BEFORE_EXECUTION. MUTATING (scratch clone only).
*  Safety:  Operates ONLY on a disposable clone (SCR_RECALL), ERASEd at the end.
*           The pinocchio fixtures are only READ (COPY source). No lane rebuild.
*
*  PURPOSE: Directly exercise RECALL's batched index re-insert (upsert) under an
*           ACTIVE CDX order -- the path the destructive script did NOT cover
*           (it cleared the order before RECALL). A/B: RECALL with the index
*           attached (batched reinsert) vs order cleared (no reinsert baseline).
*
*  EXPECT (after the 1.3d batching fix):
*    - RA RECALL ALL under active order completes in ~scan time (tens of s), NOT
*      the O(n^2) minutes the per-row-commit path would have cost.
*    - RA ELAPSED ~= RB ELAPSED (batched reinsert is negligible vs scan + DBF).
*    - Integrity: after RA, a keyed SEEK on a recalled SID is ~ms (its index key
*      was reinserted); COUNT DELETED = 0.
*
*  RUN (host):
*    powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\dottalkpp\data\scripts\pinocchio\run_pinocchio_recall_proof_teed.ps1
* ============================================================
SET ECHO OFF
SET TIMER ON
SET TALK OFF

SET PATH DBF DBF/pinocchio
SET PATH INDEXES INDEXES/pinocchio
SET PATH LMDB LMDB/pinocchio

* cleanup any leftover scratch
CLOSE
ERASE TABLE SCR_RECALL CONFIRM

ECHO === R0. clone STUDENTS (1M), build index, attach active order ===
SELECT 0
USE STUDENTS
COPY TO SCR_RECALL AS X64 OVERWRITE
USE SCR_RECALL
COUNT
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG SID
BUILDLMDB HUGE CLEAN YES
SET INDEX TO SCR_RECALL
SET ORDER TO TAG SID

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* RA. RECALL ALL under ACTIVE order -> exercises batched upsert reinsert
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO === RA. delete ~9999, then RECALL ALL under ACTIVE order (batched reinsert) ===
SET ORDER TO TAG SID
DELETE FOR SID > 50990000
COUNT DELETED
ECHO --- RA: RECALL ALL (time this; index attached, so reinsert is batched) ---
RECALL ALL
COUNT DELETED
ECHO --- RA integrity: recalled key 50999999 must be back in the index (fast keyed SEEK) ---
SEEK 50999999
SMARTLIST SID,LNAME,FNAME NEXT 1

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* RB. RECALL ALL under CLEARED order (index closed) -> baseline (no reinsert)
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO === RB. delete ~9999, then RECALL ALL under CLEARED order (no reinsert) ===
SET ORDER TO TAG SID
DELETE FOR SID > 50990000
COUNT DELETED
SET ORDER TO PHYSICAL
ECHO --- RB: RECALL ALL (time this; index closed, no reinsert = baseline) ---
RECALL ALL
COUNT DELETED

ECHO === R9. cleanup: ERASE SCR_RECALL ===
CLOSE
ERASE TABLE SCR_RECALL CONFIRM

ECHO ============================================================
ECHO RECALL BATCHING PROOF COMPLETE. Confirm:
ECHO   RA RECALL ALL completed in ~scan time (NOT O(n^2) minutes).
ECHO   RA ELAPSED ~= RB ELAPSED (batched reinsert negligible -> surcharge gone).
ECHO   RA integrity: SEEK 50999999 is ~ms and Found (index key reinserted).
ECHO   COUNT DELETED after each RECALL = 0.
ECHO ============================================================
